South Africa to Train Toolmakers to Stem Shortage, Business Report Says

-- B y   A n a   M o n t e i r o
-- 
2011-03-30T05:28:06Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/south-africa-to-train-toolmakers-to-stem-shortage-business-report-says.html
South Africa , which has a shortage
of 50,000 toolmakers, wll partner with 100 groups through the
 Department of Trade and Industry  to provide people with
training that meets U.S. and German standards,  Business Report 
said.  Certificates issued to trainees who complete a nine-month
course at one of South Africa’s education and training
authorities don’t meet standards, the Johannesburg-based
newspaper cited Toolmakers Association of South Africa President
Bob Williamson as saying.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Ana Monteiro at 
 amonteiro4@bloomberg.net  